{
  "stem": "9538.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when they had planned an uprising and the Germans heard about it and they found an arsenal of weapons on the 31st of October, 1942, these 16 young men were marched to the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they knew what was up with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SOBBING] They were singing the which is the national anthem of Israel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were singing the and marching to the [GERMAN] where they had to stand up and were-- with machine guns.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A machine gun was already there waiting for them with a German SS, and they were shot down.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the 31st of October, 1942.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Things like that happened all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On this-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I mean, people were dying and starving to death.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and I mean, I can't go into details.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother managed to-- she, at that time, worked in the ghetto in a-- oh gosh, I must look dreadful-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Let's call it as a dress-maker.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had to repair German uniforms, which came from the Eastern Front.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had to repair them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were workshops, then, in the ghetto, and she worked there with other women.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father already had been killed, and I worked as a nurse until the 2nd of November, 1943. 7 o'clock in the morning I had to go to the hospital if I wasn't on night duty.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't let any of the groups go to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The columns were all assembled and they didn't let anybody go to work on the 2nd of November, '43.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I thought, this is very peculiar.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But then, eventually, they marched the columns out through the gates.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They went to their work places.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
